PALINDROME PROGRAM: Exercise 2 on page 383:

We have written an iterative version of a palindrome
function in the program in this directory.  We leave
it to the reader to write a recursive version.

Our program is in C++; the reader may wish to rewrite
it in C.  In our program, we hard-wired the input
file to be

   /usr/dict/words

which is a file of words found on UNIX systems that is
convenient to use.  To test your palindrome function,
you can use any text file.

